# Customize Connection

With implementing the `ITransport` interface, you can connect to SecuX in your own way.

## Requirements
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) version >= `14` or above (which can be checked by running `node -v`). You can use nvm for managing multiple Node versions on a single machine installed.

## Installation
```bash npm
npm install @secux/transport
```

## Implement the interface
Once you finish the following abstract function, you can start your journey with SecuX.
```js
import { ITransport } from "@secux/transport";

class MyTransport extends ITransport {
  constructor() {
    super(
      {
        // The maximum packet size is 64 bytes via USB.
        packetSize: 64,  
        // Each signing execution needs at most 1 seconds, and
        // a command contains at most 15 signing executions.
        timeout: 20000, // 15 execution time + 5 transmission time (sec)
      }
    );
  }

  async Connect(): Promise<void> { /* your implementation */ }

  async Disconnect(): Promise<void> { /* your implementation */ }

  async Write(data: Buffer): Promise<void> { /* your implementation */ }

  // call this function when data is received.
  sealed protected ReceiveData(data: Buffer): void;
}
```

:::caution notice

You must monitor the receiving data, and call `this.ReceiveData()` to complete the data flow.

function Example(props) {
  // -------------------- implementation start --------------------
  class MyTransport extends ITransport {
    static get CONFIGURATION_ID() { return 1; }
    static get INTERFACE_ID() { return 0; }
    static get ENDPOINT_ID() { return 1; }

    constructor(device) {
      super();

      this.device = device;
    }

    async Connect() {
      try {
        await this.device.open();
        await this.device.selectConfiguration(MyTransport.CONFIGURATION_ID);
        await this.device.claimInterface(MyTransport.INTERFACE_ID);

        this.Listener();
      } catch (e) {
        throw e;
      }
    }

    async Disconnect() {
      if (this.device.opened) {
        await this.device.releaseInterface(MyTransport.INTERFACE_ID);
        await this.device.reset();
        await this.device.close();
      }
    }

    async Write(data) {
      const result = await this.device.transferOut(MyTransport.ENDPOINT_ID, data);

      if (result.status !== "ok") {
        throw Error(
          `Failed to write data to device, \
          got transfer status "${result.status}".`
        );
      }

      if (result.bytesWritten !== data.length)
        throw Error(
          `Failed to write data to device, \
          expect write "${data.length}" bytes, \
          but "${result.bytesWritten}" bytes written.`
        );
    }

    async Read() {
      const receive = await this.device.transferIn(MyTransport.ENDPOINT_ID, 64);

      if (receive.status !== "ok") {
        throw Error(
          `Failed to read data from device, \
          got transfer status "${receive.status}".`
        );
      }

      if (receive.data) return Buffer.from(receive.data.buffer);
      return Buffer.alloc(0);
    }

    Listener() {
      const interval = 1;
      const receive = async () => {
        if (!this) return;

        const data = await this.Read();
        if (data.length > 0) this.ReceiveData(data);

        setTimeout(receive, interval);
      };

      receive();
    }
  }
  // -------------------- implementation end --------------------


  const [address, setAddress] = useState('');

  async function Connect() {
    const device = await navigator.usb.requestDevice(
      { 
        filters: [ 
          { vendorId: 0x1915, productId: 0x4297 } 
        ] 
      }
    );
    const transport = new MyTransport(device);

    await transport.Connect();

    // query Bitcoin address (native segwit)
    const btcAccount = await transport.getAddress("m/84'/0'/0'/0/0");
    setAddress(btcAccount);

    await transport.Disconnect();
  }

  return (
    <div>
      <Button onClick={Connect}/>
      <h2>{address}</h2>
    </div>
  );
}
